column1: #Text=The Milwaukee Bucks defeated the visiting Orlando Magic 93 - 89 at BMO Harris Bradley Center on Friday evening .
#Text=The Bucks ( 6 - 7 ) came into this game winners of five of their last six games , but the Bucks ( 6 - 8 ) were able to pull away in the second half .
#Text=Giannis Antetokounmpo was the high - point man for the Bucks , as he finished with 21 points , 11 rebounds , 10 assists , five steals and three blocks , in 39 minutes .

column1: #Text=Jabari Parker followed up with 22 points ( 8 - 17 FG , 5 - 7 3Pt , 1 - 5 FT ) , three rebounds , three assists and three steals , in 35 minutes , while Jason Terry chipped in four points on 2 - of - 4 shooting , in 20 minutes off the bench .
#Text=The Bucks have now lost two in a row , while the Magic have now lost five of their last six games .
#Text=Nikola Vucevic shot just 4 - of - 12 from the field on his way to 11 rebounds .
#Text=Evan Fournier scored 18 points on 6 - of - 13 shooting in 37 minutes , while Fournier scored 18 points on 6 - of - 13 shooting in 37 minutes .
#Text=The Magic shot just 42 percent from the field , but struggled from long range , where they shot just 42 percent .
#Text=Up next , the Bucks will head home Friday to take on the Pistons , while the Magic will head home Friday and play the Bulls .
